2 unit(s) Beyond Meat®
113 g Mirepoix
300 g Red Potato
2 tbsp Gravy Spice Blend
2 unit(s) Garlic, cloves
14 g Parsley and Thyme
2 unit(s) Beef Broth Concentrate
2 unit(s) Sandwich Bun
½ tbsp Soy Sauce
1 tsp Garlic Salt
56 g Green Peas
2.33 tbsp Oil*
1 tbsp Unsalted Butter*
0.13 tsp Pepper*
0.13 tsp Salt*

Quarter potatoes.
Add potatoes and 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil to a parchment-lined baking sheet. Season with half the garlic salt and pepper, then toss to coat.
Roast in the middle of the oven, until tender and golden-brown, 25-28 min.

Meanwhile, strip 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) thyme leaves from stems.
Roughly chop parsley.
Peel, then mince or grate garlic.
Heat a large pot over medium-high heat.
When the pot is hot, add 1 tsp (2 tsp) oil, then Beyond Meat® patties. Cook, breaking up patties into smaller pieces, until crispy, 5-6 min.**
Season with salt and pepper.
Using a slotted spoon, transfer Beyond Meat® to a large bowl.
Carefully discard excess fat in the pot.

Reduce heat to medium, then add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) butter, mirepoix, thyme, remaining garlic salt and half the garlic to the same pot.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until mirepoix softens slightly, 3-4 min.
Add Beyond Meat® and any juices from the bowl.
Sprinkle Gravy Spice Blend over top.
Cook, stirring often, until veggies and Beyond Meat® are coated, 1-2 min.

Add broth concentrate, soy sauce, peas and 1 1/2 cups (3 cups) water to the pot.
Season with salt and pepper, then stir to combine. Bring to a boil over high.
Once boiling, reduce heat to medium-low.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until stew thickens slightly and veggies are tender, 10-12 min. (TIP: If you prefer a looser stew, add an additional 1/4 cup [1/2 cup] water!)

Meanwhile, combine remaining garlic and 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil in a small bowl.
Halve buns. Arrange on an unlined baking sheet, cut-side up.
Brush with garlic oil.
Toast in the top of the oven, until light golden-brown, 5-6 min. (TIP: Keep an eye on buns so they don't burn!)

Add roasted potatoes to stew, then stir to combine.
Divide Irish-style stew between bowls.
Serve garlic crostini alongside.
Sprinkle parsley over stew and crostini.

If you've opted to get Beyond Meat®, season it in the same way the recipe instructs you to season the beef. To cook Beyond Meat®, pan-fry over medium-high heat, breaking up patties into bite-sized pieces, until crispy, 5-6 min.** Follow the rest of the recipe as written.